tc_game_config_files.template:
// These are a reasonable set of defaults for a CSPromod server. You // probably don't need to (and shouldn't) change the values other than // those near the top.
hostname "$[HostName]" rcon_password "$[RConPassword]" sv_password "$[PrivatePassword]"
log on
sv_lan 0 sv_maxupdaterate 100 sv_minupdaterate 20 sv_maxcmdrate 100 sv_voiceenable 1
mp_buytime 15 mp_c4timer 35 mp_forcecamera 0 mp_footsteps 1 mp_falldamage 1
mp_freezetime 5 mp_friendlyfire 0 mp_maxrounds 0 mp_roundtime 105 mp_timelimit 25 mp_startmoney 800 mp_autoteambalance 1 mp_limitteams 2
sv_accelerate 5 //do NOT change anything in this block sv_stopspeed 75 sv_maxspeed 320 sv_friction 4 sv_gravity 800 //ok, resume tampering
sv_netgraph_allow_traffic 0 sv_allowdownload 1 sv_allowupload 1 sv_alltalk 0 sv_deadchat 1 sv_cheats 0 net_maxfilesize 32 sv_maxrate 131072 sv_minrate 3500 sv_timeout 65 sv_voicecodec vaudio_speex
mp_allowspectators 1 mp_decals 300 decalfrequency 60 sv_pausable 0 setpause 0 sv_clockcorrection_msecs 0 unpause
sv_master_legacy_mode "0" // Use old (outside-of-Steam) code to communicate with master servers.
sv_region "255" // This console variable is queried by the server browser to determine what part of the world the server is in. // Value Location // 0 US - East // 1 US - West // 2 South America // 3 Europe // 4 Asia // 5 Australia // 6 Middle East // 7 Africa // 255 World (default) // Please note: // If sv_region is set to a specific region (0 to 7) then the server will be listed if this region or "<All>" is selected in the Steam server browser's location filter. // If sv_region is set to anything else then the server will only be listed if "<All>" is selected in the Steam server browser's location filter.
// I'm awake aka Forces heartbeat of master servers heartbeat
